# econ_proxy shared secret.
#
# Copy this file to `.env` (gitignored) and set a strong value, then
# `docker compose up -d`. docker compose auto-loads `.env` from this directory.
#
#   cp .env.example .env
#   echo "ECON_PROXY_TOKEN=$(openssl rand -hex 32)" > .env
#
# When set, /economic-calendar requires a matching ?apikey=<token> (else 401);
# /health stays open. Set the device's CONFIG_STOCK_FMP_API_KEY to the SAME value.
# Leave empty for an open LAN-only deployment (no auth) — but it is REQUIRED once
# the proxy is exposed publicly (Cloudflare tunnel / AWS).
#
# NOTE: the CI/CD workflow injects this from the GitHub repo secret
# ECON_PROXY_TOKEN, so a server deployed only via CD does not need this file.
# It's the belt-and-suspenders for manual `docker compose up` on the host.
ECON_PROXY_TOKEN=
